
## Webapt:
 [scala, spray.io, h2:mem]
* get pings over http in http://domain/pings path form clients
	(colect ip form hosts with DHCP)
* create /etc/ansible/hosts file from pings
 	(in future give input for ansible - $ANSIBLE_PATH)
* insert deb repository and copy to clients
* show all aivalible packages and allow to mark package be required or not (or without any policy)
* make install, update, upgrade by ansible
* allow create text file (i.e. config), config path and copy to clients by ansible
* allow to run command on clients by ansible

## pinger:
 [vala]
* ping to server and send their hostname (carry ip)
* configurable by file /etc/default/pinger.conf

## pkgmgr:
 [scala]
* get deb links
* return aivalible packages
* return dependences for package - list of packages
